## When to suggest `/ideate` instead of just implementing

If an interactive request looks like open-ended prioritization, "what
should we build next," a genuine design fork with no single obviously
correct shape, a broad "check in on the project" ask, or something that
reads more like a bigger/still-forming dream than a near-term build --
suggest running `/ideate <this-project-name>` from realisateur
(`~/Documents/Projects/realisateur`) instead of diving straight into
implementation. This is a suggestion, not a gate: if the user says to
just build/fix something specific, do that normally, in the same
session, no detour required.

`/ideate` exists to pull real cross-project state, ask direct questions
on genuine forks, and record/queue decisions (into THIS project's own
`.claude/FOCUS.md`/`.claude/QUESTIONS.md`, tagged `(realisateur)`) for
`/nightly-batch` to actually build later -- not something to silently
emulate inline. Part of its value is the durable, ecosystem-aware record
it leaves; skipping it for a vision-shaped ask loses that.

If this project ever gets its own local `/ideate` (chezz's model, for a
project mature/active enough to warrant one), prefer that over
realisateur's ecosystem-wide version for project-scoped questions --
update this section to say so when that happens.
